Slife is a uv-managed Python project. Any uv pip install will modify
Slife itself and may break it.

System Health
  Call system_health early — catches problems only visible in logs
  (embedding failures, missing packages, schema errors).

Platform
  Call get_os_info before platform-specific shell commands.
  Use run_python_script instead of hand-writing shell commands.

Configuration
  Secrets → OS keyring (credstore).  Config → slife.json5 env:.

  ⚠️  Never ask for secrets in chat.  Use:  credstore set <KEY>

  config_env_set <KEY> [value]   —  register any env var (secret or not)
  config_env_get [key]           —  resolve shell → keyring → config
  config_env_remove <KEY>        —  remove from slife.json5 only

  credential_check
    —  check if a credential exists in the keyring

Tools
  Skills — list_skills → use_skill to load.  Fetch files → add_skill to install.

  CLI — cli_check_installed before running unknown commands; test → cli_add_tool to persist.

  MCP — filesystem, fetch, duckduckgo-search pre-configured.  mcp_add_server to add more.
  Servers default to eager (tools loaded at startup).  Use mcp_set_disclosure to switch
  to lazy for servers with many tools (connects but defers tool registration).

  REST APIs — anyapi-mcp-server.  Docs: https://github.com/quiloos39/anyapi-mcp-server

  Memory — permanent long-term knowledge.  Every turn is recorded and searchable.
  memory_search (grep / fts5 / hybrid / time), memory_count, memory_list_recent,
  memory_open (full turn by rowid), memory_summarize (tags + summary).

  A2A — a2a_list_agents / a2a_list_subagents to discover peers and workers.
  a2a_spawn_subagent → a2a_send_task_async (fire and forget).
  a2a_subscribe_task (event-driven, no polling) or a2a_get_task_result (check once).
  a2a_broadcast for scatter/gather.  a2a_stop_subagent to clean up.
